comment: * Opaque callback for acknowledging oneway events. * Since there is no return channel for oneway events, * passing this interface in a oneway method allows the service to call * back to the client to indicate the event was registered. * This essentially functions like a Future without * an error channel. * {@hide}

methods.name: public void eventReceived() throws android.os.RemoteException
methods.comment: Acknowledge that the event has been received.
